-- Yell in Debt Restructuring Talks, Sunday Telegraph Says
-- B y   I s a a c   A r n s d o r f
-- 2012-03-25T11:02:03Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-25/yell-in-debt-restructuring-talks-sunday-telegraph-says.html
Yell Group Plc (YELL) , publisher of the
U.K.’s Yellow Pages, will appoint a banking adviser to help
restructure billions of pounds in debt, the Sunday Telegraph
said, citing people it didn’t identify.  The Berkshire, U.K.-based company has been talking to
investment banks including  Goldman Sachs (GS)  and  Greenhill & Co. (GHL) 
before negotiating with lenders about relaxing banking covenants
for 2014, the newspaper reported.  Jon Salmon, a spokesman for Yell, declined to comment via
phone today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Isaac Arnsdorf in London at 
 iarnsdorf@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
